description: Many of us assume that professional success depends on being brave or wholly original. Susan Tabor-Kleiman dispels this notion, showing how even a risk averse, conventional girl who grew up in the Midwest can move seamlessly from trial lawyer to nonprofit work to business owner—and how you too can forge your path to success.
title: Closing Keynote–Climbing Down the High Dive: A Cautious Girl’s Path to Success
